# SOP-002: Periodic Task Management System

**Document Owner:** Prime MIS  
**Department:** MIS  
**System:** Periodic Task Management Google Sheet  
**Version:** 1.0.0  
**Status:** Active  
**Applies To:** MIS Executive, Senior MIS Executive  
**Estimated Time:** 5–15 Minutes  
**Prerequisite:** SOP-001 – Daily Checklist System

---

# 1. Purpose

This SOP explains how to configure, assign, monitor, and review recurring business tasks that occur on a Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Half-Yearly, or Yearly basis.

This system is maintained separately from the Daily Checklist System to reduce sheet size, improve performance, and simplify task management.

---

# 2. Scope

This SOP applies to all recurring operational and management tasks that are not performed daily.

Examples include:

- Weekly Reports
- Monthly Reports
- Quarterly Reviews
- Half-Yearly Reviews
- Annual Activities

---

# 3. Supported Task Frequencies

| Frequency | Code | Example |
|------------|------|---------------------------|
| Weekly | W | Weekly Sales Summary |
| Monthly | M | Monthly Sales Report |
| Quarterly | Q | Quarterly Business Review |
| Half-Yearly | H | Half-Year Performance Review |
| Yearly | Y | Annual Stock Audit |

---

# 4. Accessing the File

Open the file using any of the following methods:

- Google Drive
- Google Site
- AppSheet

File Name:

**Periodic Task Management System**

---

# 5. One-Time Setup

The initial setup is identical to SOP-001.

Verify the following before using the system:

- Script Authorization Completed
- Week List Updated
- Working Day Calendar Updated
- Holiday List Updated
- Doer List Updated

If any of these are incomplete, complete SOP-001 before proceeding.

---

# 6. Task Creation Procedure

## Step 1 – Open Task List

Navigate to the **Task List** sheet.

---

## Step 2 – Enter Task Details

Complete the following fields:

- Task Name
- Doer Name
- Department
- Frequency
- Planned Date
- Remarks (if required)

---

## Step 3 – Select Frequency

Choose the appropriate frequency.

Examples:

| Task | Frequency |
|------|-----------|
| Weekly Sales Report | W |
| Monthly MIS Report | M |
| Quarterly Review Meeting | Q |
| Half-Year Performance Review | H |
| Annual Inventory Audit | Y |

---

## Step 4 – Submit

Click the **Submit** button.

Verify the Status changes to **Sent**.

---

# 7. Verification

Open the **Master** sheet and confirm:

- Task Created Successfully
- Correct Doer Assigned
- Correct Department
- Correct Frequency
- Correct Planned Date
- No Formula Errors

---

# 8. Dashboard Review

Open the **Dashboard** sheet.

Verify:

- Pending Tasks
- Completed Tasks
- Completion Percentage
- Department Performance
- Employee Performance
- Overdue Tasks

---

# 9. Common Errors

| Problem | Possible Cause | Recommended Solution |
|----------|----------------|----------------------|
| Wrong Frequency Selected | Incorrect Code | Update Frequency |
| Duplicate Task | Submit Clicked Twice | Delete Duplicate Record |
| Task Missing | Script Failure | Re-submit Task |
| Dashboard Incorrect | Formula Deleted | Restore Formula |
| Incorrect Due Date | Calendar Issue | Update Calendar |

---

# 10. Troubleshooting

If a recurring task is not generated:

1. Verify Script Authorization.
2. Check Week List.
3. Verify Working Day Calendar.
4. Check Holiday List.
5. Confirm Frequency Code.
6. Re-submit the Task.
7. Contact Senior MIS Executive if unresolved.

---

# 11. Quality Checklist

Before closing the reporting period, verify:

- [ ] All recurring tasks created.
- [ ] Dashboard updated.
- [ ] Pending tasks reviewed.
- [ ] No duplicate tasks.
- [ ] Reports generated successfully.
- [ ] Management informed where applicable.

---

# 12. Learning Objectives

After completing this SOP, the trainee should be able to:

- Understand the Periodic Task Management System.
- Create recurring tasks correctly.
- Select the correct frequency.
- Verify task generation.
- Monitor completion status.
- Resolve common issues.

---

# 13. AI Trainer Instructions

The AI Trainer should:

- Explain the purpose of the Periodic Task Management System.
- Demonstrate task creation for each frequency.
- Explain when each frequency should be used.
- Simulate common errors.
- Ask practical questions before moving to the next lesson.

---

# 14. Assessment

The trainee must successfully:

- Create one Weekly task.
- Create one Monthly task.
- Create one Quarterly task.
- Create one Half-Yearly task (if applicable).
- Create one Yearly task.
- Verify each task in the Master sheet.
- Explain the difference between each frequency.

Minimum Competency Level:

**Level 3 – Competent**

